                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1635: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 11, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. With regard to decision of Diplomatic Corps in Addis Ababa to request their
                    respective Governments to call to the attention of the <pb facs="0995" n="893"
                        xml:id="pg_893"/> Italian Government the special position of the open cities
                    of Addis Ababa and Diredawa containing as they do several thousand foreign
                    residents, we would be glad to have a report of any action that may have been
                    taken by the Governments now represented at Addis Ababa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
